author: rich
msg: Refactoring in the Page Flow compiler (annotation processor) area:
- Added a layer of abstraction between the annotation processors and Sun's Mirror APIs.
- Extracted core code into a new module (compiler-core), and removed all use of Java5 features (generics, etc.).
This will allow Page Flow to (possibly) compile under JDK1.4, using a (currently nonexistant) processing layer like XDoclet or JAM.
tests: netui bvt, drt in trunk (WinXP)
